==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pathic
<hw>Path"ic</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧th"⟦icr⟧c)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pathicus</ets>, Gr. <grk>paqiko`s</grk>, passive, fr.
<grk>paqei^n</grk>, <grk>pa`schei^n</grk>, to suffer]</ety> <def>A male
who submits to the crime against nature; a catamite.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<note>⟦hand⟧ The term ⟦ldquo⟧crime against nature⟦rdquo⟧ to refer to
homosexual activity is now (2002) seldom used except by religious
conservatives. It was in the 1913 Webster, and is left here for
historical purposes.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pathic</ent>⟦br⟧

